  "question": "John drives for 3 hours at a speed of 60 mph and then turns around because he realizes he forgot something very important at home.  He tries to get home in 4 hours but spends the first 2 hours in standstill traffic.  He spends the next half-hour driving at a speed of 30mph, before being able to drive the remaining time of the 4 hours going at 80 mph.  How far is he from home at the end of those 4 hours?",
  "prompt": "John drives for 3 hours at a speed of 60 mph and then turns around because he realizes he forgot something very important at home.  He tries to get home in 4 hours but spends the first 2 hours in standstill traffic.  He spends the next half-hour driving at a speed of 30mph, before being able to drive the remaining time of the 4 hours going at 80 mph.  How far is he from home at the end of those 4 hours?\n\nShow your work briefly and put the final answer in \\boxed{}.",
  "gold_answer": "45",
  "generated_text": "To find the total distance John is from home at the end of the 4 hours, we need to break down his journey into the segments described:\n\n1.  **First segment:**\n    *   Speed: $60$ mph\n    *   Time: $3$ hours\n    *   Distance: $60 \\text{ mph} \\times 3 \\text{ hr} = 180$ miles\n    *   Since this is driving *away* from home, his position relative to home is $+180$ miles.\n\n2.  **Second segment (Standstill):**\n    *   Speed: $0$ mph\n    *   Time: $2$ hours\n    *   Distance: $0$ miles\n    *   He stays at the current location ($+180$ miles).\n\n3.  **Third segment:**\n    *   Speed: $30$ mph\n    *   Time: $0.5$ hours ($\\frac{1}{2}$ hour)\n    *   Distance: $30 \\text{ mph} \\times 0.5 \\text{ hr} = 15$ miles\n    *   He is driving away from home (since he was at 180 miles and drove for 2 hours, he is still moving away from home before this).\n    *   New position: $180 + 15 = 195$ miles.\n\n4.  **Fourth segment:**\n    *   Time remaining: $4 \\text{ hours (total)} - 2 \\text{ hours (standstill)} - 0.5 \\text{ hours (driving)} = 1.5$ hours.\n    *   Speed: $80$ mph\n    *   Distance: $80 \\text{ mph} \\times 1.5 \\text{ hr} = 120$ miles.\n    *   He is driving away from home (he was at 195 miles and drove for 2 hours, so he is still moving away from home).\n    *   New position: $195 + 120 = 315$ miles.\n\n**Total Distance from Home:**\nThe final position is 315 miles from home.\n\n\\boxed{315}\n",
